  <h1>About Me</h1>
  <p>
    Hi there! I’m <strong>Garrett</strong>, a manufacturing systems engineer living in <strong>northern Indiana</strong>.
  </p>

  <p>
    By day, I spend my time tackling the intricate challenges of manufacturing systems. By night—and whenever else I can find the time—I’m likely deep in the weeds of a project that blends my professional engineering background with my passion for technology and the physical world.
  </p>

  <h2>What I’m Up To</h2>
  <p>
    My life is a constant rotation of learning, building, and exploring. Here’s a look at what currently occupies my headspace:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Smart Home & Automation:</strong> I’m a dedicated tinkerer in the world of home automation. Whether it's <strong>Home Assistant</strong>, <strong>Zigbee</strong>, or <strong>ESPHome</strong>, I spend plenty of weekends writing YAML scripts and refining my setup to make my home run just a little bit smarter.</li>
    <li><strong>Software Development:</strong> I am currently <strong>learning Rust</strong>. I’m particularly passionate about the <strong>Arnis</strong> project, where I use OpenStreetMap data to procedurally generate Minecraft worlds.</li>
    <li><strong>Photography:</strong> I have a keen eye for capturing the action. My photography focus includes <strong>sporting events</strong>, <strong>live concerts</strong>, and <strong>wildlife/animal portraiture</strong>.</li>
    <li><strong>Aerospace & Building:</strong> I have a strong interest in high-altitude endeavors and hardware engineering, including <strong>weather balloon hunting</strong> and <strong>building drones</strong> from the ground up.</li>
    <li><strong>High-End Tech & Audio:</strong> I keep a close eye on the latest developments in audio and visual tech, always interested in the nuance between high-fidelity equipment and the evolving landscape of home media.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Life at Home</h2>
  <p>
    When the screens are off and the soldering iron is cold, you’ll usually find me spending time with <strong>Peeta</strong>, my remarkably affectionate and playful tabby cat. He’s the undisputed foreman of my home office and a constant companion.
  </p>

  <p>
    I’m a fan of progressive rock, especially the intricate soundscapes of <strong>Yes</strong>—the <em>Fragile</em> album remains a personal favorite that I find myself returning to again and again.
  </p>


